Indonesia Stock Movers: Astra International, Berau Coal, Garuda

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-08-18T09:15:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/indonesia-stocks-aneka-tambang-astra-international-berau-coal.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  advanced 67.72 points, or 1.7
percent, to 4,020.99. The market was closed yesterday for a
public holiday.  PT Astra International (ASII IJ),  Indonesia ’s largest
automotive retailer, gained 3.9 percent to 72,750 rupiah, the
highest close since July 27. The country’s vehicle sales rose 27
percent in July from a month earlier to 89,056 units, the
highest monthly sales this year, Kontan reported, citing Jonfis
Fandy, marketing director at PT Honda Prospect Motor.  Sales in the first seven months of the year increased 14.5
percent to 506,743 units, according to the report. Three calls
to Honda Prospect’s office in Jakarta weren’t answered.  PT Berau Coal Energy (BRAU IJ), a coal producer, added 5.8
percent to 550 rupiah, the highest close since Aug. 3. First-
half net income jumped to $76.4 million from $17.1 million a
year earlier, the company said in a statement published in
 Bisnis Indonesia .  PT Garuda Indonesia (GIAA IJ), the nation’s largest
airline, surged 8.9 percent to 490 rupiah, the steepest increase
since its Feb. 11 debut. Bisnis Indonesia reported the company’s
July net profit jumped 81 percent from the same month a year
earlier to 320 billion rupiah ($37.4 million). Pujobroto, a
company spokesman, didn’t return a call made to his mobile
phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
